{
  "stem": "25651.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "I mean, he loved me because I was his dolly.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "But when people played with the dolly, in preference to him, he had quite a problem with that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "He had another problem, and that was because we were swapping over to becoming Czech as a family, so the emphasis was to get us all into Czech schools.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "So Emmanuel, when he had to start in his first class when he was six-- we used to have a-- a maid who was German, and she sort of brought him up, you know, next to his mother, obviously.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "So until he was five, he had this Czech-- this German maid.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And he was most upset when my parents let her go in 1932.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And the new maid came, who was Czech, [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "Leeda. ?] And [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "Leeda ?] was like the second woman in my life because there was my mother and there was [?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "Leeda. ?] And [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "Milos ?] never took to [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "Leeda ?] because he wanted his-- his old-- the maid from before who-- who loved him and who-- whom he loved.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "And he spoke German.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "He's the only one amongst us who wasn't immediately bilingual.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my mother always spoke German or Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She spoke German to us because German was the language of culture.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yiddish was the language of folk type of-- when she wanted to say something pithy, she would say it in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So did my father, as a matter of fact.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, Yiddish was spoken a lot because of my mother's benevolent nature.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My mother was extraordinary in-- in her benevolence.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, good works.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
